  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Trim and bash the lemongrass stalk and galangal. Trim and thinly slice the spring onions, peel the garlic and crush using the back of your knife."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Place a saucepan on medium heat with neutral oil. Once hot, cook the red Thai curry paste until fragrant, 1-2 mins. Add in the lemongrass, galangal, crushed garlic cloves and Makrut lime leaves. Pour in the stock, stir and let it come to a boil. Once boiling, place a lid on, turn the heat to medium-low and let infuse for 10-15 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, trim and halve the green beans. Discard the stalks from the shiitake and thinly slice. Cook the rice noodles according to package directions."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once the broth has infused, remove and discard the bits in it. Turn the heat up to medium-high and add the spring onion whites, green beans, cherry tomatoes and shiitake. Cook until the green beans are tender but still have a crunch, 3-4 mins. Remove from the heat and taste and season with lime juice and fish sauce."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Share the noodles between your bowls and pour over the soup base, making sure to share the veggies. Scatter over the spring onion greens and serve with any remaining lime wedges."
    }
  ],
